	   LISTVIEW New	Methods:
 
		.------------------
		. SortColumn Method
 
		The SortColumn method sorts one	to four	columns	of 
		a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.SortColumn	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Column=]{col}:
						[*Type=]{type}[:
						[*Mask=]{mask}][:
						[*Column1=]{col1}][:
						[*Type1=]{type1}][:
						[*Mask1=]{mask1}][:
						[*Column2=]{col2}][:
						[*Type2=]{type2}][:
						[*Mask2=]{mask2}][:
						[*Column3=]{col3}][:
						[*Type3=]{type3}][:
						[*Mask3=]{mask3}]
 
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW into which an item is 
			inserted.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that returns 
			0 for success.
 
		col	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable 
			that specifies the column to be	sorted.
 
		type	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable 
			that specifies the type	of sort.
 
		mask	is an optional Character String	Variable or literal
			that specifies date of time mask.
 
		col1-3	is a optional decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the column to be	sorted.
 
		type1-3	is a optional decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the type	of sort.
 
		mask1-3	is an optional Character String	Variable or literal
			that specifies a date of time mask.
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. A type value must be one of:
		 
			1 - Alpha Ascending
			2 - Alpha Descending
			3 - Numeric Ascending
			4 - Numeric Descending
			5 - Date Ascending
			6 - Date Descending
			7 - Time Ascending
			8 - Time Descending
			9 - Timestamp Ascending
			10 - Timestamp Descending
 
		  2. A date mask value looks for dd for	day, mm	for month,
		     yy	or yyyy	for year.  The default mask is:	mm-dd-yy
 
		  3. A time mask value looks for hh for	hour, mm for minute,
		     ss	for seconds, and xx for	100th of a second. 
		     The default mask is: hh:mm:ss.xx
 
		  4. A timestamp mask value looks for DD for day, 
		     MM	for month, YY or YYYY for year,	hh for hour,
		     mm	for minute, ss for seconds, and	xx for 100th of
		     a second.	The default mask is: YYYYMMDDhhmmssxx
 
		.--------------------
		. InsertItemEx Method
		.
 
		The InsertItemEx method	inserts	a new item into	
		a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.InsertItemEx	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Text=]{text}[:
						[*Index=]{index}][:
						[*Image=]{image}][:
						[*Param=]{param}][:
						[*State=]{state}][:
						[*Statemask=]{statemask}][:
						[*SubItem1=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem2=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem3=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem4=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem5=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem6=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem7=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem8=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem9=]{stext}][:
						[*SubItem10=]{stext}]]
 
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW into which an item is inserted.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that returns 
			the new	item's index.
 
		text	is a required Character	String Variable	or literal
			that specifies the label associated with the new item.
 
		index	is an optional Numeric Variable	that specifies 
			the new	item's index.
 
		image	is an optional Numeric Variable	that specifies
			an IMAGELIST object index to associate with 
			the item.
 
		param	is an optional decimal number or Numeric Variable
			that specifies a user defined value.
 
		state	is an optional decimal number or Numeric Variable
			that specifies initial item state as described below.
 
		statemask	is an optional decimal number or Numeric 
				Variable that specifies	the valid state
				values as described below.
 
		stext	is an optional Character String	Variable or literal
			that specifies the test	associated with	a subitem 
			in the new item.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. The optional {state} value	determines the 
		     item's initial state as follows:
 
		     Value   Constant		 Initially the item ...
		     0x01    LVIS_FOCUSED	 has the focus and is 
						 surrounded by a standard
						 focus rectangle.  Although
						 more than one item may	be
						 selected, only	one item can
						 have the focus.
		      0x02    LVIS_SELECTED	 is selected.  The 
						 appearance of a selected
						 item depends on whether 
						 it has	the focus and the
						 system	colors used to 
						 indicate selection.
		       0x04    LVIS_CUT		 is marked.
		       0x08    LVIS_DROPHILITED	 is highlighted	as a
						 drag-and-drop target.
 
		  2. The optional {statemask} is a value from the table
		     above which indicates the valid initial state values.
 
		  3. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	new item
		     number or zero if the method fails.
 
		  4. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
 
		  5. If	{return} is too	small to contain the new item number,
		     the OVER Condition	Flag is	set (TRUE).
 
		  6. The EOS Condition Flag is always cleared (FALSE).
 
