		.---------------------
		. FindItemCheck	Method
		.
		The SetItemCheck method	sets a checkmark beside	an 
		item within a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.FindItemCheck	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [[*Start=]{start}]
 
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW that is modified.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that indicates
			the index of the next item with	a checkmark.
 
		start	is an optional decimal number or Numeric
			Variable that specifies	the item to start 
			checking at.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. {start} is	a zero based number indicating the item	to
		     start the search with.
		     The default is zero.
		  2. If	no item	is found, {result} will	be 0xFFFFFFFF
		  3. The OVER and EOS Condition	Flags are always 
		     cleared (FALSE).
		  4. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
 
		.-------------------------
		. SetImageListState Method
		.
		 
		The SetImageListState method associates	an IMAGELIST
		object with the	state icons of a LISTVIEW.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.SetImageListState [GIVING {return}]:
					     USING [*ImageList=]{imagelist}
		Where:
 
		label	   is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	   is a	required LISTVIEW that is modified.
 
		return	   is an optional Numeric Variable that	indicates
			   the success or failure of the method.
 
		imagelist  is a	required IMAGELIST that	contains 
			   the images or bitmaps.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. Any icons or bitmaps displayed in the {object} will be
		     obtained from {imagelist}.
		  2. {imagelist} must been previously created.
		  3. The images	will be	associated with	the object's 
		     state icons.
		  4. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	status of
		     the modification as follows.
		     $TRUE and $FALSE are defined in PLBEQU.INC.
 
			  Value	  Constant	  The association ...
			  0	  $FALSE  failed.
			  1	  $TRUE	  was successful.
		  5. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)	
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
		  6. The OVER and EOS Condition	Flags are always 
		     cleared (FALSE).
 
		.----------------------
		. InsertColumnEx Method
 
		The InsertColumnEx method inserts a new	column into
		a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.InsertColumnEx	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Text=]{text}:
						[*Width=]{width}:
						[*Index=]{index}[:
						[*Format=]{format}][:
						[*Image=]{image}][:
						[*Order=]{order}]
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW into which a column
			is inserted.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that returns
			the new	column number.
 
		text	is a required Character	String Variable	or literal
			that specifies the label for the new column.
 
		width	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the width of the	new column.
 
		index	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the index of the	subitem	for 
			the new	column.
 
		format	is an optional decimal number or Numeric Variable 
			that specifies the label justification and column
			options	as described below.
 
		image	is an optional decimal number or Numeric Variable
			that specifies the small image displayed in the	
			column header.
		 
		order	is an optional decimal number or Numeric Variable 
			that specifies the order the column is placed in.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. Columns must be inserted before any sub-items are added.
  
		  2. The optional {format} value is a constant as defined
		     in	PLBMETH.INC or a numeric variable indicating one 
		     of	the following label justifications:
 
			  Value	  Constant	  The column is	...
			  0x00	  LVCFMT_LEFT	  left justified. (default)
			  0x01	  LVCFMT_RIGHT	  right	justified.
			  0x02	  LVCMFT_CENTER	  centered.
 
			  0x0800  LVCFMT_IMAGE		 column	has an image
			  0x1000  LVCFMT_BITMAP_ON_RIGHT image should be
							 displayed on the
							 right
   
		  3. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	new column
		     number or -1 if the method	fails.
		  4. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
		  5. If	{return} is too	small to contain result	of the method,
		     the OVER Condition	Flag is	set (TRUE).
		  6. The EOS Condition Flag is always cleared (FALSE).
		  7. Integer values for	the following can integer values
		     can be found in the PLBMETH.INC include.
 
			 LVCFMT_LEFT		 Integer 4,"0x0000"
			 LVCFMT_RIGHT		 Integer 4,"0x0001"
			 LVCFMT_CENTER		 Integer 4,"0x0002"
 
			 LVCFMT_IMAGE		 Integer 4,"0x0800"
			 LVCFMT_BITMAP_ON_RIGHT	 Integer 4,"0x1000"
			 LVCFMT_COL_HAS_IMAGES	 Integer 4,"0x8000"
 
		.----------------------
		. SetColumnImage Method
		.
 
		The SetColumnImage method set the small	icon image to
		display	for a column within a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.SetColumnImage	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Index=]{index}:
						[*Image=]{image}
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW that is modified.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that indicates 
			the success or failure of the method.
 
		index	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the column to modify.
 
		image	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable 
			that specifies new image index.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. {index} is	a zero based number indicating the column
		     within the	object to modify.
		  2. {image} is	a zero based number indicating the new image 
		     index within the object's small imagelist.
		  3. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	status of 
		     the modification as follows.  $TRUE and $FALSE are
		     defined in	PLBEQU.INC.
 
			  Value	  Constant	  The modification ...
			  0	  $FALSE  failed.
			  1	  $TRUE	  was successful.
		 
		     If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
 
		    4. The OVER	and EOS	Condition Flags	are always 
		       cleared (FALSE).
 
		.----------------------
		. SetColumnOrder Method
		.
 
		The SetColumnOrder method sets order for a column within a
		LISTVIEW object.  The method uses the following	format:
 
		[label]	{object}.SetColumnOrder	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Index=]{index}:
						[*Order=]{order}
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW that is modified.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that indicates 
			the success or failure of the method.
 
		index	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies the column to modify.
 
		order	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable 
			that specifies the new column order.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. {index} is	a zero based number indicating the column
		     within the	object to modify.
		  2. {order} is	a zero based number indicating the order the
		     column should be placed within the	object's columns.
		  3. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	status of
		     the modification as follows.  $TRUE and $FALSE are
		     defined in	PLBEQU.INC.
 
			  Value	  Constant	  The modification ...
			  0	  $FALSE  failed.
			  1	  $TRUE	  was successful.
 
		     If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)	
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
 
		  4. The OVER and EOS Condition	Flags are always cleared
		     (FALSE).
 
		.----------------------
		. SubItemHitTest Method
		.
		The SubItemHitTest method returns the item and subitem 
		number,	in a LISTVIEW object, given a point on the screen.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.SubItemHitTest	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Horz=]{horz}:
						[*Vert=]{vert}
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW object to be accessed.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that returns the 
			item/subitem number.
 
		horz	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable that
			specifies the horizontal position to test.
 
		vert	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable that
			specifies the vertical position	to test.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. Upon completion, {return} will contain -1 on a failure.
		  2. On	success	{return} is the	item number * 100 + the	
		     subitem number.
		  3. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
		  4. The OVER and EOS Condition	Flags are always cleared
		     (FALSE).
 
		.-------------------
		. GetItemRect Method
		.
		The GetItemRect	method returns the bounding rectangle for a
		specified item in a LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.GetItemRect	[GIVING	{return}]:
						USING [*Index=]{index}:
						[*Subitem=]{subitem}
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW object to be accessed.
 
		return	is an optional Character String	Variable that returns
			the item's rectangle.
 
		index	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable that
			specifies the item accessed.
 
		subitem	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable that
			specifies the sub-item number.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. {index} is	a zero based number indicating the item
		     within the	object to access.
		  2. {sub-item}	specifies that the rectangle is	to come	from
		     a child item (column) of {index}.
		  3. Upon completion, {return} will contain the	specified
		     item's bounding rectangle as:
			
			ttttbbbbllllrrrr - where t - top
						 b - bottom
						 l - left 
						 r - right
			
		  4. If	{return} is too	small to contain the text string, the
		     EOS Condition Flag	is set (TRUE).
		  5. The OVER and ZERO Condition Flags are always cleared
		     (FALSE).
 
		.-----------------------
		. EnableScrollBar Method
		.
		The EnableScrollBar method enables or disables the 
		scrollbars in a	LISTVIEW object.
		
		The method uses	the following format:
 
		[label]	{object}.EnableScrollBar [GIVING {return}]:
						 USING [*Enable=]{enable}
 
		Where:
 
		label	is an optional Program Execution Label.
 
		object	is a required LISTVIEW object to be accessed.
 
		return	is an optional Numeric Variable	that gets the 
			return value.
 
		enable	is a required decimal number or	Numeric	Variable
			that specifies 0 to disable or 1 to enable the 
			scrollbars.
 
		Flags Affected:	EOS, OVER, ZERO
 
		Note the following:
 
		  1. If	the value returned is zero, the	ZERO (or EQUAL)
		     Condition Flag is set (TRUE).
		  2. The OVER and EOS Condition	Flags are always 
		     cleared (FALSE).
 
 
	 - A new event named ItemActivate has been added for the
	   LISTVIEW object.
 
	   ItemActivate	Event
 
	       $ITEMACTIVATE	 EQU	25
 
	       The ItemActivate	event occurs when the mouse button 
	       is pressed and released over an item in a LISTVIEW 
	       object.
 
	       Note the	following:
 
	       1. The ItemActivate event is referenced using an	event value
		  of twenty-five (25).
		  The equated label in PLBEQU.INC for this event 
		  is $ITEMACTIVATE.
	       2. This event depends on	the setting of the ACTIVATE
		  property.
	       3. The Event Result value is the	item 
		  number * 100 + the subitem number.
	       4. The Event Modifier contains a	value from the 
		  following table:
 
		      Value   Key Pressed
			1	ALT
			2	CTRL
			4	SHIFTS
			
